## Detailed changes

### 1. `src/types/dashboard.ts` — Remove `DATASET_SUPPORTED_DISPLAY_TYPES` (lines 301-384)

Delete the entire `DATASET_SUPPORTED_DISPLAY_TYPES` constant and its 27-line JSDoc block. No other code references it.

### 2. `src/commands/dashboard/resolve.ts` — Trim `validateWidgetEnums` (lines 620-655)

Remove the import of `DATASET_SUPPORTED_DISPLAY_TYPES` from the import block (line 27).

Remove lines 639-654 (the cross-validation block). The function becomes:

```typescript
export function validateWidgetEnums(display?: string, dataset?: string): void {
  if (
    display &&
    !DISPLAY_TYPES.includes(display as (typeof DISPLAY_TYPES)[number])
  ) {
    throw new ValidationError(
      `Invalid --display value "${display}".\nValid display types: ${DISPLAY_TYPES.join(", ")}`,
      "display"
    );
  }
  if (
    dataset &&
    !WIDGET_TYPES.includes(dataset as (typeof WIDGET_TYPES)[number])
  ) {
    throw new ValidationError(
      `Invalid --dataset value "${dataset}".\nValid datasets: ${WIDGET_TYPES.join(", ")}`,
      "dataset"
    );
  }
}
```

### 3. `test/commands/dashboard/widget/add.test.ts` (lines 215-229)

Replace "throws ValidationError for big_number with issue dataset" with a test that verifies the widget is **created successfully** with `displayType: "big_number"` and `widgetType: "issue"`.

### 4. `test/commands/dashboard/widget/edit.test.ts` (lines 185-246)

Two tests use the now-removed cross-validation:

- **"throws ValidationError when --dataset change produces invalid combo with existing display"** (lines 185-215): Change to verify the edit succeeds — changing dataset to `issue` on a `big_number` widget should work.

- **"throws ValidationError when --display change produces invalid combo with existing dataset"** (lines 217-246): This tests `preprod-app-size` + `table`. Same fix — verify the edit succeeds.

